issue_comments.body:
@alexism @liyintang @jun-he I agree that `byte[]` is more general. The proposed feature, if it's implemented at all, doesn't belong in this composable, modular handler. It's no different than the encryption that snuck in here somehow. Handlers are most useful when they do and assume as little as possible. If a handler is insufficient by itself, you can decorate its behavior with your own.

I strongly discourage weakening or otherwise reducing the generality of the Kafka handler to solve a specific issue, especially one for which the conditions are incidental and arbitrary, like the ratio of one kind of process to another. A stateful behavior, such as this, or any superfluous transformation that isn't a strict requirement of adapting the pipeline to a Kafka producer belongs in a distinct handler. By saying "no" to new features, you're implicitly saying "yes" to those who need an un-opinionated adapter.

_Such is the magic of Plog._

